# issue
* psalm seems to have less of an issue when defining DATA as a simple `array`, but this leads `key-of` to resolve to `array-key`, which then causes issues with `@return ID` on a method that returns `string`.
* `InvalidDocblock` seems to mess with the expected templated param count, I'm wondering if this would be mitigated by resolving "invalid" template to `as mixed` to suppress `TooManyTemplateParams` ?
* `MismatchingDocblockReturnType` is raised seemingly directly as a result of `key-of<DATA>` failing to parse.

as always, there's always the possibility that I'm grossly misusing psalm :P


# repro
* https://psalm.dev/r/0135f229d6
* using b19d256

```php
<?php
/**
* @template DATA as array<string, scalar|array|object|null>
* @template ID_VAL as array-key
*/
abstract class Foo {
  /**
  * @var DATA
  */
  protected $data;
  
  /**
  * @param DATA $data
  */
  public function __construct(array $data) {
    $this->data = $data;
  }
  
  /**
  * @template K as key-of<DATA>
  *
  * @param K $property
  *
  * @return DATA[K]
  */
  public function __get(string $property) {
    return $this->data[$property];
  }
  
  /**
  * @return ID_VAL
  */
  public function ObtainRepoId() {
    return $this->__get(static::IdProperty());
  }
  
  /**
  * @return key-of<DATA>
  */
  abstract public static function IdProperty() : string;
}

/**
* @template-extends Foo<array{id:int, name:string}, 'id', int>
*/
class Bar extends Foo {
  public static function IdProperty() : string {
    return 'id';
  }
}


/**
* @template-extends Foo<array{id:int, name:string}, 'id', int>
*/
class Baz extends Foo {
  public static function IdProperty() : string {
    return 'id';
  }
}
```
